1
00:00:02,936 --> 00:00:05,239
Why are my eyes so swollen, you ask?

2
00:00:06,139 --> 00:00:09,910
Last night, my puppy-like boyfriend
and I...

3
00:00:10,477 --> 00:00:11,245
Wow...

4
00:00:11,979 --> 00:00:15,716
I can't! Just thinking about it
makes me cry again.

5
00:00:18,852 --> 00:00:20,621
I'm not looking back anymore.

6
00:00:23,190 --> 00:00:24,424
Good morning.

7
00:00:26,560 --> 00:00:29,129
Suzuki, could you organize
those bills?

8
00:00:31,665 --> 00:00:34,067
She's wearing glasses today?

9
00:00:34,968 --> 00:00:35,702
Yes.

10
00:00:35,736 --> 00:00:38,105
Have you returned the accessories yet?

11
00:00:38,138 --> 00:00:39,439
I'll get on it.

12
00:00:40,207 --> 00:00:41,074
Glasses?

13
00:00:41,909 --> 00:00:42,809
Yes.

14
00:00:43,243 --> 00:00:44,711
Ms. Suzuki.

15
00:00:45,412 --> 00:00:46,179
Glasses?

16
00:00:47,114 --> 00:00:47,881
Yes.

17
00:00:49,449 --> 00:00:51,084
- Suzuki?
- Yes?

18
00:00:52,019 --> 00:00:53,453
Your eyes are swollen.

19
00:00:54,855 --> 00:00:56,290
Please don't ask.

20
00:00:57,024 --> 00:00:58,625
Did something happen?

21
00:00:59,726 --> 00:01:01,228
Don't remind me.

22
00:01:01,862 --> 00:01:03,697
Lunch is on us.

23
00:01:03,730 --> 00:01:06,700
Cart passing. Move please.

24
00:01:09,136 --> 00:01:10,537
Ms. Horai...

25
00:01:13,874 --> 00:01:17,077
We are transporting large items.
Don't block the hall.

26
00:01:19,880 --> 00:01:23,750
Is she really never going to
come back to Miyavi?

27
00:01:26,653 --> 00:01:27,421
That's it.

28
00:01:30,357 --> 00:01:31,959
Really beautiful.

29
00:01:33,093 --> 00:01:34,628
This will be the cover shot.

30
00:01:40,334 --> 00:01:42,703
- Suzuki?
- Junnosuke...?

31
00:01:46,006 --> 00:01:46,940
Where?

32
00:01:49,609 --> 00:01:50,877
Hey, stop!

33
00:01:53,380 --> 00:01:54,581
Junnosuke?

34
00:01:55,716 --> 00:01:57,417
Huh? What?

35
00:01:57,451 --> 00:01:59,820
I'm so sorry.

36
00:01:59,853 --> 00:02:00,921
Are you okay, Suzuki?

37
00:02:02,456 --> 00:02:04,358
Over there, too.

38
00:02:06,560 --> 00:02:07,961
Junnosuke.

39
00:02:09,096 --> 00:02:12,265
I'm really very sorry.

40
00:02:12,299 --> 00:02:14,568
What's wrong with you?
Snap out of it.

41
00:02:14,601 --> 00:02:16,203
Here he is again.

42
00:02:17,037 --> 00:02:18,538
What's wrong with her?

43
00:02:18,905 --> 00:02:20,207
White Jun!

44
00:02:23,276 --> 00:02:26,313
- What are you...
- Hey, stop it!

45
00:02:26,346 --> 00:02:27,781
Don't!

46
00:02:27,814 --> 00:02:30,283
Seems pretty serious.

47
00:02:30,317 --> 00:02:33,520
She saw Hinata, the model,
and was like, "Junnosuke!"

48
00:02:33,520 --> 00:02:36,690
She's the daughter of Sae Ebisawa,
the actress, right?

49
00:02:36,990 --> 00:02:38,258
She must be scary.

50
00:02:38,291 --> 00:02:40,527
You don't even want to know.

51
00:02:40,560 --> 00:02:43,630
She made sure we didn't
let any word out about this.

52
00:02:43,663 --> 00:02:46,833
She's so worked up
about making a stunning debut.

53
00:02:49,369 --> 00:02:50,971
Junnosuke...

54
00:02:52,839 --> 00:02:53,607
No, it's not.

55
00:02:56,276 --> 00:02:57,110
What?

56
00:03:02,282 --> 00:03:03,150
Here.

57
00:03:05,652 --> 00:03:08,955
When your heart is empty,
fill it with something else.

58
00:03:11,258 --> 00:03:12,559
Thank you.

59
00:03:12,592 --> 00:03:15,062
But Mr. Nakazawa lent me one
the other day.

60
00:03:15,462 --> 00:03:16,396
He did?

61
00:03:18,098 --> 00:03:19,132
I had a feeling...

62
00:03:19,833 --> 00:03:21,501
that you were crying again.

63
00:03:22,969 --> 00:03:23,804
Can I sit?

64
00:03:31,511 --> 00:03:33,280
You broke up with him?

65
00:03:37,984 --> 00:03:40,353
What it means to work...

66
00:03:41,588 --> 00:03:44,124
What it means to dream...

67
00:03:48,361 --> 00:03:53,800
Sometimes it means
you have to give something up.

68
00:03:57,037 --> 00:04:00,774
You gave up something
that precious to you.

69
00:04:01,508 --> 00:04:03,577
You have to make
that dream come true now.

70
00:04:07,781 --> 00:04:08,648
Yes.

71
00:04:21,428 --> 00:04:23,330
He really knows what to say.

72
00:04:25,298 --> 00:04:27,968
Put it behind you and cheer up.

73
00:04:28,368 --> 00:04:30,637
Put all that negative energy
into work.

74
00:04:33,607 --> 00:04:34,508
She's right.

75
00:04:35,408 --> 00:04:38,545
I chose this path.
I'm going to do my best.

76
00:04:40,147 --> 00:04:43,483
I wonder if Junnosuke
is working hard at his new job too.

77
00:04:43,750 --> 00:04:47,320
I hope my son Junnosuke
will be of service to you too.

78
00:04:47,921 --> 00:04:49,156
Please.

79
00:04:49,823 --> 00:04:52,359
I envy you for having such a fine son.

80
00:04:53,660 --> 00:04:55,896
He still has much to learn.

81
00:04:55,929 --> 00:04:57,664
Yes. I'll do my best.

82
00:04:59,833 --> 00:05:02,068
- Please.
- Thank you.

83
00:05:02,402 --> 00:05:03,503
Shall I?

84
00:05:08,508 --> 00:05:11,244
Ever since I became editor-in-chief,

85
00:05:11,278 --> 00:05:15,949
three brands requested
to break their ad contracts.

86
00:05:18,185 --> 00:05:20,253
Times are tough. It's not your fault.

87
00:05:21,788 --> 00:05:25,025
It had to be Reiko.

88
00:05:26,793 --> 00:05:28,695
I have my pride, too.

89
00:05:31,131 --> 00:05:34,301
Please let me stand down
from this position.

90
00:05:34,834 --> 00:05:37,070
- But...
- It's fine.

91
00:05:38,305 --> 00:05:39,573
I realized.

92
00:05:41,474 --> 00:05:45,178
That maybe I just wanted
whatever Reiko had.

93
00:05:47,647 --> 00:05:48,748
Miyavi.

94
00:05:50,650 --> 00:05:51,451
And you.

95
00:05:55,422 --> 00:05:56,923
I'm sorry.

96
00:05:58,959 --> 00:06:01,595
- But my feelings are...
- I'm kidding.

97
00:06:05,098 --> 00:06:08,235
Anyways. Miyavi doesn't need me.

98
00:06:09,769 --> 00:06:10,704
It needs Reiko.

99
00:06:15,942 --> 00:06:17,644
Equipment Management

100
00:06:27,220 --> 00:06:28,922
Is it almost your break time?

101
00:06:30,390 --> 00:06:31,658
Mr. Ugajin.

102
00:06:33,193 --> 00:06:36,796
Won't you come back to Miyavi
once the equipment is organized?

103
00:06:37,564 --> 00:06:39,099
The board has agreed to it.

104
00:06:42,802 --> 00:06:44,170
Thank you.

105
00:06:44,638 --> 00:06:47,407
But I cannot go back anymore.

106
00:06:49,175 --> 00:06:51,645
And why is that?

107
00:06:53,113 --> 00:06:53,913
I...

108
00:06:56,716 --> 00:07:00,420
Taking responsibility
is the only way for me to live.

109
00:07:02,689 --> 00:07:05,191
I'm really grateful for your offer.

110
00:07:05,825 --> 00:07:08,528
But, I'm sorry.

111
00:07:11,431 --> 00:07:14,167
My break is over. Goodbye.

112
00:07:18,438 --> 00:07:19,372
Have a tangerine.

113
00:07:27,881 --> 00:07:32,652
So, I'll be the temporary
editor-in-chief.

114
00:07:32,686 --> 00:07:34,321
I hope to do my best.

115
00:07:34,988 --> 00:07:37,757
- Editor-in-chief?
- Don't strain yourself.

116
00:07:38,258 --> 00:07:42,028
Find someone to listen to your woes
after work hours.

117
00:07:50,036 --> 00:07:51,504
I've finished ten.

118
00:07:51,538 --> 00:07:52,939
I've finished 20,

119
00:07:54,274 --> 00:07:54,574
Deputy editor-in-chief

120
00:07:54,574 --> 00:07:56,476
Let's do them all today.

121
00:07:56,876 --> 00:07:58,144
Editor-in-chief!

122
00:08:00,980 --> 00:08:02,282
What is it?

123
00:08:02,816 --> 00:08:05,051
Our photographs have been leaked!

124
00:08:06,086 --> 00:08:08,254
What, let me see.

125
00:08:10,990 --> 00:08:14,661
These are Hinata's photographs,
the ones for the cover.

126
00:08:14,694 --> 00:08:17,130
All the ones we were using
have been leaked.

127
00:08:17,163 --> 00:08:18,832
It's on Instagram, too.

128
00:08:19,899 --> 00:08:21,401
But this was top secret.

129
00:08:21,601 --> 00:08:23,503
This is really bad.

130
00:08:23,536 --> 00:08:25,905
We were so careful
about not getting it out.

131
00:08:26,072 --> 00:08:28,608
The debut of actress Sae Mizusawa's
daughter.

132
00:08:29,476 --> 00:08:32,712
This was a super important
surprise project.

133
00:08:32,746 --> 00:08:34,914
We need to contact Hinata right away.

134
00:08:35,815 --> 00:08:37,183
You're right.

135
00:08:37,417 --> 00:08:39,219
You have a call, Mr. Handa.

136
00:08:59,305 --> 00:09:03,476
Oh My Boss! Love Not Included

137
00:09:03,943 --> 00:09:08,014
All the time and money I put into
Hinata's debut.

138
00:09:08,648 --> 00:09:10,150
And it's all gone to waste.

139
00:09:10,583 --> 00:09:12,085
I'm so sorry.

140
00:09:12,118 --> 00:09:15,055
What value do your words have?

141
00:09:15,522 --> 00:09:16,923
I'm done with you.

142
00:09:18,858 --> 00:09:20,660
But, please...

143
00:09:24,764 --> 00:09:29,002
She's really mad. What do we do?

144
00:09:29,169 --> 00:09:33,173
Without Hinata, we'd have to think
of a whole new cover.

145
00:09:33,673 --> 00:09:35,575
We don't have time for that.

146
00:09:36,509 --> 00:09:37,744
Please.

147
00:09:38,211 --> 00:09:40,847
You're the only one who can save us.

148
00:09:40,880 --> 00:09:42,115
Please save us!

149
00:09:42,749 --> 00:09:44,017
It doesn't concern me.

150
00:09:44,584 --> 00:09:45,685
But...

151
00:09:46,419 --> 00:09:48,455
You don't care about Miyavi anymore?

152
00:09:49,456 --> 00:09:50,256
Right.

153
00:09:51,991 --> 00:09:53,526
Ms. Horai!

154
00:09:56,896 --> 00:10:01,234
Are leaked photographs
that big of a problem?

155
00:10:02,302 --> 00:10:03,403
Sure...

156
00:10:06,873 --> 00:10:11,578
Thank you for celebrating
my promotion as editor-in-chief.

157
00:10:11,878 --> 00:10:13,346
It's all thanks to you.

158
00:10:14,047 --> 00:10:17,217
We're faced with
the worst situation ever.

159
00:10:17,250 --> 00:10:20,353
- But let's work together and...
- He's here!

160
00:10:20,553 --> 00:10:23,089
- Come on in.
- Over here.

161
00:10:23,123 --> 00:10:24,290
Come on.

162
00:10:24,858 --> 00:10:25,925
Junnosuke?

163
00:10:27,861 --> 00:10:28,828
Why are you here?

164
00:10:29,996 --> 00:10:31,231
Where's Oashi?

165
00:10:31,631 --> 00:10:37,303
You were so depressed,
we had Oashi call him over.

166
00:10:37,804 --> 00:10:40,773
As your senpai,
we're going to be your cupids now.

167
00:10:40,807 --> 00:10:42,442
This isn't the time for that.

168
00:10:42,475 --> 00:10:43,977
Doesn't matter.

169
00:10:49,916 --> 00:10:51,751
I thought you were celebrating my...

170
00:10:51,784 --> 00:10:54,287
I'm sure you just need to
talk it through.

171
00:10:55,054 --> 00:10:57,323
Come on, go on.

172
00:10:57,357 --> 00:10:59,359
- Ask him how he's doing.
- Right.

173
00:11:01,728 --> 00:11:03,196
How are you doing?

174
00:11:04,430 --> 00:11:06,533
Yeah, it's only been four days.

175
00:11:07,233 --> 00:11:08,234
You're right.

176
00:11:09,068 --> 00:11:12,772
- Were you in Tokyo for work today?
- Good one.

177
00:11:12,805 --> 00:11:15,108
Yes, meeting clients with my father.

178
00:11:15,408 --> 00:11:18,244
I had a tight schedule
the whole day today.

179
00:11:19,012 --> 00:11:21,114
Meetings and stuff.

180
00:11:21,147 --> 00:11:24,684
I met a lot of people.
It was kind of hard.

181
00:11:24,984 --> 00:11:25,852
That's what he said.

182
00:11:28,154 --> 00:11:30,690
Are you sure about
quitting photography?

183
00:11:30,723 --> 00:11:34,360
I don't think we're in the position
to ask him that.

184
00:11:35,161 --> 00:11:38,398
It's okay. I was going to
take over the business anyway.

185
00:11:38,431 --> 00:11:39,933
That was the original plan.

186
00:11:41,334 --> 00:11:42,502
But...

187
00:11:43,970 --> 00:11:48,474
It wasn't me that
Dad really wanted to run the company.

188
00:11:51,844 --> 00:11:55,214
I'm going back to Kanazawa
once I'm done meeting clients.

189
00:11:57,183 --> 00:11:58,952
Good luck working too, Nami.

190
00:11:59,953 --> 00:12:01,754
I'll be going now.

191
00:12:02,488 --> 00:12:03,623
Goodbye.

192
00:12:05,892 --> 00:12:08,394
Wait, Mr. Junnosuke?

193
00:12:11,831 --> 00:12:14,867
Okay, shall we drink
to my promotion now?

194
00:12:15,201 --> 00:12:17,904
What? Are we not going to?

195
00:12:23,076 --> 00:12:24,243
Hey.

196
00:12:27,447 --> 00:12:30,750
I was just leaving too.
Want to go for some ramen?

197
00:12:30,783 --> 00:12:32,852
100 Ramen

198
00:12:36,823 --> 00:12:38,191
Welcome.

199
00:12:40,760 --> 00:12:43,162
Miso ramen, large, hard noodles.

200
00:12:43,696 --> 00:12:44,764
Pork ramen.

201
00:12:46,633 --> 00:12:49,402
Here you go. There.

202
00:12:49,869 --> 00:12:50,803
Thanks.

203
00:12:51,771 --> 00:12:52,739
Thanks.

204
00:12:55,174 --> 00:12:58,811
I guess rich families
have their troubles too.

205
00:13:00,146 --> 00:13:01,080
Not really.

206
00:13:11,157 --> 00:13:12,258
You know what?

207
00:13:14,594 --> 00:13:17,630
When I saw you working the other day.

208
00:13:18,564 --> 00:13:21,901
I could tell you enjoyed your job
as a photographer.

209
00:13:21,934 --> 00:13:24,537
And that you took pride in it.

210
00:13:27,674 --> 00:13:28,875
I admired you.

211
00:13:37,016 --> 00:13:38,217
How about Suzuki?

212
00:13:40,019 --> 00:13:40,953
Is it really over?

213
00:13:45,191 --> 00:13:46,325
What can I say?

214
00:13:47,660 --> 00:13:49,562
Nami has her own dream now.

215
00:13:53,599 --> 00:13:54,500
Yeah.

216
00:13:57,070 --> 00:14:02,642
But you need to try harder
to make her understand.

217
00:14:04,844 --> 00:14:06,512
Or nothing is going to change.

218
00:14:12,018 --> 00:14:14,320
Life is full of twists and turns.

219
00:14:15,521 --> 00:14:17,490
Gosh, you're really the man.

220
00:14:20,560 --> 00:14:22,695
Hi, Mom.

221
00:14:22,729 --> 00:14:26,299
I sent you a package today.
Eat it with Junnosuke.

222
00:14:26,332 --> 00:14:28,067
Horse sashimi, your favorite.

223
00:14:30,103 --> 00:14:31,337
Sorry, Mom.

224
00:14:33,940 --> 00:14:36,175
I broke up with him.

225
00:14:40,713 --> 00:14:41,781
Oh, did you?

226
00:14:44,517 --> 00:14:46,786
I'm going to work hard now.

227
00:14:47,620 --> 00:14:51,224
And live a normal average life
for myself.

228
00:14:51,958 --> 00:14:52,892
Nami.

229
00:14:53,559 --> 00:14:58,197
I used to say normal was best
all this time.

230
00:14:58,564 --> 00:15:01,000
But I've been thinking lately.

231
00:15:01,801 --> 00:15:04,570
That whatever you choose for yourself,

232
00:15:05,037 --> 00:15:06,806
whoever you choose to be with,

233
00:15:07,340 --> 00:15:11,611
if you just do your best
in every situation,

234
00:15:11,644 --> 00:15:16,048
that will become
what's normal for you.

235
00:15:19,118 --> 00:15:20,486
What's normal for me?

236
00:15:21,120 --> 00:15:22,488
Listen to me.

237
00:15:22,989 --> 00:15:27,927
Whatever you choose to do,
I'll be your number one fan.

238
00:15:30,296 --> 00:15:31,430
Me too!

239
00:15:33,299 --> 00:15:35,401
Your father says the same.

240
00:16:15,107 --> 00:16:16,909
The path I chose.

241
00:16:20,513 --> 00:16:22,548
- We are very sorry.
- Forgive us.

242
00:16:23,316 --> 00:16:27,453
Mom's furious,
but I'm really not that mad.

243
00:16:28,187 --> 00:16:30,022
It was good publicity for me.

244
00:16:30,590 --> 00:16:31,591
Publicity?

245
00:16:32,525 --> 00:16:34,827
I'm in a band.

246
00:16:35,695 --> 00:16:37,763
But nobody comes to see us.

247
00:16:38,297 --> 00:16:41,400
Our next gig
is before the magazine comes out.

248
00:16:41,901 --> 00:16:46,038
Mom had told me not to tell anybody
about my model debut.

249
00:16:46,939 --> 00:16:49,575
But thanks to the leak,
our tickets sold out.

250
00:16:50,476 --> 00:16:51,344
Lucky me!

251
00:16:52,144 --> 00:16:54,513
I'll convince Mom.

252
00:16:55,615 --> 00:16:58,150
We've been given permission
to do another shoot.

253
00:16:58,184 --> 00:17:00,219
She said she'll persuade her mother.

254
00:17:01,354 --> 00:17:02,555
I'm so relieved.

255
00:17:02,855 --> 00:17:08,427
But still, it's already been leaked.
How do we retake it?

256
00:17:08,461 --> 00:17:11,464
The surprise factor is gone now.

257
00:17:11,497 --> 00:17:13,499
It's not going to be as impactful.

258
00:17:15,268 --> 00:17:16,302
Um...

259
00:17:17,536 --> 00:17:20,973
Why don't we use the leak
as publicity?

260
00:17:21,674 --> 00:17:22,608
What do you mean?

261
00:17:22,808 --> 00:17:26,579
Like using the leaked pictures
to create a bigger surprise.

262
00:17:27,613 --> 00:17:28,948
I see.

263
00:17:28,981 --> 00:17:33,619
That way, the leaked pictures
will work as publicity for us.

264
00:17:34,520 --> 00:17:36,789
I get where you're coming from.

265
00:17:36,956 --> 00:17:40,192
But how do we create
that bigger surprise?

266
00:17:41,928 --> 00:17:43,562
We can brainstorm.

267
00:17:45,965 --> 00:17:48,601
Let's turn this predicament
into an opportunity.

268
00:17:48,634 --> 00:17:51,604
Let's think. That's our job, isn't it?

269
00:17:53,906 --> 00:17:55,575
Yeah, it sure is.

270
00:17:57,343 --> 00:18:01,047
All right, let's do it. Together.

271
00:18:01,747 --> 00:18:02,715
Yes!

272
00:18:05,518 --> 00:18:09,622
We can do lighter makeup
to make her look more natural.

273
00:18:09,655 --> 00:18:11,757
But the dress is really flashy.

274
00:18:11,791 --> 00:18:13,159
Please!

275
00:18:13,192 --> 00:18:15,661
I told you, I can't.

276
00:18:15,695 --> 00:18:18,597
- We're begging you.
- Just one more time!

277
00:18:18,631 --> 00:18:22,802
Mr. Takashima. We're very sorry
for the trouble we're causing you.

278
00:18:22,835 --> 00:18:26,772
But we need to do it
with the same people.

279
00:18:29,675 --> 00:18:32,845
Mr. Nakazawa.
Thank you for helping us out.

280
00:18:32,878 --> 00:18:33,813
Thank you.

281
00:18:34,347 --> 00:18:38,317
It's nothing.
That's what teams are for.

282
00:18:38,351 --> 00:18:40,953
You really say such nice things.

283
00:18:40,953 --> 00:18:42,221
Let's make a calendar.

284
00:18:42,688 --> 00:18:45,825
Nice words, then harsh words.
Alternately.

285
00:18:45,858 --> 00:18:46,959
Who'll buy that?

286
00:18:46,993 --> 00:18:48,594
I'm not really sure.

287
00:18:49,028 --> 00:18:52,031
- Nice words, then harsh words.
- Yeah right.

288
00:18:59,772 --> 00:19:01,007
Later, Izumi.

289
00:19:03,542 --> 00:19:04,910
Mr. Nakazawa.

290
00:19:08,681 --> 00:19:10,583
You're a real masochist.

291
00:19:12,685 --> 00:19:13,786
What the heck?

292
00:19:15,287 --> 00:19:16,122
Because...

293
00:19:17,323 --> 00:19:20,926
You know it'll be unrequited.

294
00:19:20,960 --> 00:19:23,896
But you still keep heading that way.

295
00:19:30,336 --> 00:19:31,437
Well...

296
00:19:32,438 --> 00:19:37,309
You could say I'm a sadist
towards myself.

297
00:19:40,680 --> 00:19:46,052
Then as a sadist, you would be happy
if you went on a boring date with me.

298
00:19:47,253 --> 00:19:49,155
What are you talking about?

299
00:19:49,955 --> 00:19:51,824
Then what if that date was fun?

300
00:19:56,595 --> 00:19:57,997
Would there be a problem?

301
00:20:00,666 --> 00:20:01,667
Izumi.

302
00:20:02,401 --> 00:20:04,203
You're really clever.

303
00:20:06,038 --> 00:20:07,006
I know.

304
00:20:13,045 --> 00:20:14,213
I'm ready.

305
00:20:14,647 --> 00:20:16,115
Thank you!

306
00:20:18,017 --> 00:20:20,186
Okay, let's do this.

307
00:20:20,653 --> 00:20:22,254
Please!

308
00:20:36,135 --> 00:20:40,873
I wonder what Junnosuke felt
when he held a camera.

309
00:20:46,345 --> 00:20:47,980
We need you.

310
00:20:48,013 --> 00:20:50,282
I'm not your editor-in-chief anymore.

311
00:20:50,316 --> 00:20:52,485
I put everything I learned from you
in it.

312
00:20:52,818 --> 00:20:54,820
You can depend on me anytime.

313
00:20:54,854 --> 00:20:56,255
I have a favor to ask of you.

314
00:20:56,288 --> 00:20:58,591
Junnosuke, can I ask you something?

315
00:20:58,624 --> 00:21:00,559
- Let's go.
- Wait!

316
00:21:09,268 --> 00:21:10,336
How is it?

317
00:21:12,404 --> 00:21:14,240
Because of the leaked photos,

318
00:21:14,273 --> 00:21:18,310
hiding her face makes the new model
seem even more mysterious.

319
00:21:19,478 --> 00:21:22,748
It's a bold concept,
using the problem as a weapon.

320
00:21:22,982 --> 00:21:25,050
I'm so relieved!

321
00:21:27,720 --> 00:21:29,088
How's the rest going?

322
00:21:29,121 --> 00:21:30,356
It's all done.

323
00:21:30,389 --> 00:21:32,424
- And you?
- Us too.

324
00:21:32,458 --> 00:21:33,659
I'll get the layout.

325
00:21:34,760 --> 00:21:37,663
All right! We made it in time.

326
00:21:37,696 --> 00:21:38,931
Yes.

327
00:21:41,767 --> 00:21:43,569
Equipment Management

328
00:21:44,637 --> 00:21:46,705
- Good morning.
- Good morning.

329
00:22:03,355 --> 00:22:04,156
Excuse me.

330
00:22:07,259 --> 00:22:08,394
I came to return this.

331
00:22:10,362 --> 00:22:11,430
You didn't read it?

332
00:22:11,463 --> 00:22:13,399
Why would I?

333
00:22:14,433 --> 00:22:18,537
I've already made it clear
that I'm not your editor-in-chief.

334
00:22:22,374 --> 00:22:24,043
Won't you please come back?

335
00:22:26,378 --> 00:22:30,649
Miyavi needs you.

336
00:22:37,256 --> 00:22:38,457
Wait.

337
00:22:42,628 --> 00:22:46,298
- Look...
- I wrote a small article in it, too.

338
00:22:47,600 --> 00:22:50,135
I put everything I learned from you
in it.

339
00:22:51,670 --> 00:22:54,506
I really want you to read it. Please.

340
00:23:15,561 --> 00:23:17,896
- Ms. Reiko.
- Mr. Ugajin.

341
00:23:19,031 --> 00:23:20,266
You know...

342
00:23:21,367 --> 00:23:24,303
I may not be vice president
for very long.

343
00:23:27,172 --> 00:23:28,741
You were a great vice president.

344
00:23:32,912 --> 00:23:34,113
Ms. Reiko.

345
00:23:35,214 --> 00:23:40,185
If you take too much responsibility,
there won't be any left for others.

346
00:23:41,086 --> 00:23:43,822
I hope you'll consider
sharing the responsibility.

347
00:23:47,226 --> 00:23:49,795
It's important to depend on others
at times.

348
00:23:51,330 --> 00:23:53,032
We humans aren't that strong.

349
00:23:54,900 --> 00:23:56,702
We don't have to be perfect.

350
00:23:59,672 --> 00:24:03,876
By the way,
you can depend on me anytime.

351
00:24:08,947 --> 00:24:09,715
Later.

352
00:24:29,468 --> 00:24:32,204
I wrote a small article in it, too.

353
00:24:32,237 --> 00:24:34,907
I put everything I learned from you
in it.

354
00:26:08,634 --> 00:26:10,536
Even if it doesn't work out,

355
00:26:11,537 --> 00:26:12,704
it's not a waste.

356
00:26:12,971 --> 00:26:14,106
What a waste.

357
00:26:15,073 --> 00:26:17,342
Enough. End of conversation.

358
00:27:53,972 --> 00:27:57,175
By Nami Suzuki

359
00:28:22,167 --> 00:28:24,870
Okay, let's begin
the editorial meeting.

360
00:28:43,188 --> 00:28:45,657
What is it? Come on, let's go.

361
00:28:46,425 --> 00:28:47,893
Jesus...

362
00:28:53,332 --> 00:28:54,499
Ms. Horai.

363
00:28:56,702 --> 00:28:57,769
I read it.

364
00:29:01,974 --> 00:29:04,910
Magazines change with time.

365
00:29:05,577 --> 00:29:06,812
As does fashion.

366
00:29:09,748 --> 00:29:13,986
But there are some things
that never change.

367
00:29:16,521 --> 00:29:18,190
The passion of the creators.

368
00:29:21,260 --> 00:29:24,863
This job gives people
the power to dream.

369
00:29:28,033 --> 00:29:32,037
The Miyavi you created has that power.

370
00:29:38,076 --> 00:29:40,045
It was a beautiful experience.

371
00:29:45,717 --> 00:29:47,219
I have a favor to ask of you.

372
00:29:50,022 --> 00:29:51,490
Let me do it again.

373
00:29:53,158 --> 00:29:54,693
Together with you.

374
00:30:02,067 --> 00:30:03,402
Ms. Horai...

375
00:30:05,437 --> 00:30:08,707
Welcome back, editor-in-chief.

376
00:30:21,586 --> 00:30:25,691
How about a feature of watches
as a metaphor for new times.

377
00:30:28,493 --> 00:30:30,562
No, a hard no.

378
00:30:30,595 --> 00:30:32,664
- Don't you have any other...
- I like it.

379
00:30:32,698 --> 00:30:33,932
Let's go with watches.

380
00:30:39,738 --> 00:30:42,674
- Let's discuss it over lunch.
- I'm going to a meeting.

381
00:30:42,708 --> 00:30:45,077
Yes, I love steak.

382
00:30:46,712 --> 00:30:48,213
I'm so hungry.

383
00:30:48,413 --> 00:30:51,083
After Mr. Kobayakawa's interview,

384
00:30:51,116 --> 00:30:53,719
we have a meeting with Mr. Arazome.

385
00:30:53,752 --> 00:30:54,619
Got it.

386
00:30:59,024 --> 00:31:00,759
Run this through the final check.

387
00:31:00,792 --> 00:31:01,893
I'll send it in.

388
00:31:02,594 --> 00:31:05,597
Could you send me
the promotional photography schedule?

389
00:31:05,630 --> 00:31:07,632
The perfume one? Okay.

390
00:31:07,666 --> 00:31:11,870
Izumi, I need to change the picture
for Mr. Kobayakawa's interview.

391
00:31:11,903 --> 00:31:13,572
Can you check this list?

392
00:31:13,605 --> 00:31:17,843
- Suzuki.
- Oh shoot, I'm sorry.

393
00:31:18,477 --> 00:31:21,913
Mr. Ogasawara,
can you do the proofreading now?

394
00:31:21,947 --> 00:31:22,814
Okay.

395
00:31:22,848 --> 00:31:24,616
Sorry we took so long.

396
00:31:24,783 --> 00:31:27,052
- Please.
- This way.

397
00:31:39,464 --> 00:31:40,298
Ms. Horai.

398
00:31:42,000 --> 00:31:42,968
Please.

399
00:32:28,513 --> 00:32:29,714
OK with corrections

400
00:32:31,383 --> 00:32:32,417
Good work.

401
00:32:34,753 --> 00:32:38,824
The latest and newest Miyavi,
OK with corrections!

402
00:32:38,857 --> 00:32:41,026
All right!

403
00:32:44,396 --> 00:32:46,264
Kazuta Oashi

404
00:32:50,902 --> 00:32:51,903
Nami?

405
00:32:52,838 --> 00:32:54,272
Can we talk?

406
00:33:14,159 --> 00:33:15,827
Thanks for coming with me.

407
00:33:17,462 --> 00:33:18,330
How's your hand?

408
00:33:22,601 --> 00:33:23,768
It's not good.

409
00:33:25,003 --> 00:33:26,738
It's over for me as a professional.

410
00:33:30,842 --> 00:33:31,776
But you know what?

411
00:33:33,078 --> 00:33:38,483
I don't regret going for my dreams.

412
00:33:40,685 --> 00:33:41,519
Yeah.

413
00:33:43,855 --> 00:33:44,623
Let's go.

414
00:33:51,429 --> 00:33:52,697
How about you?

415
00:33:57,335 --> 00:33:59,204
Do you regret anything?

416
00:34:00,672 --> 00:34:01,573
Me?

417
00:34:02,173 --> 00:34:03,742
Yeah, who else? Dummy.

418
00:34:04,476 --> 00:34:07,145
I'm asking
if you're regretting anything.

419
00:34:09,514 --> 00:34:12,484
I asked you to come with me
for my surgery...

420
00:34:15,253 --> 00:34:20,158
because I wanted to bask
in your kindness as a farewell.

421
00:34:23,194 --> 00:34:26,798
Sorry for being such a selfish girl.

422
00:34:31,202 --> 00:34:34,773
But I'm okay now.

423
00:34:37,042 --> 00:34:38,209
So...

424
00:34:40,712 --> 00:34:43,148
You can be selfish too, you know.

425
00:34:45,383 --> 00:34:46,117
Okay?

426
00:34:50,722 --> 00:34:52,824
Go for it, Junnosuke Horai!

427
00:35:11,042 --> 00:35:12,944
Oashi

428
00:35:15,981 --> 00:35:17,515
Yeah, Oashi?

429
00:35:18,583 --> 00:35:19,584
It's Nami.

430
00:35:22,587 --> 00:35:24,756
I'd deleted your number.

431
00:35:27,258 --> 00:35:30,929
Junnosuke, can I ask you something?

432
00:35:32,797 --> 00:35:33,732
What is it?

433
00:35:35,934 --> 00:35:37,936
Will you be my boyfriend?

434
00:35:40,305 --> 00:35:41,172
Your boyfriend?

435
00:35:41,806 --> 00:35:42,640
Yes.

436
00:35:44,743 --> 00:35:45,944
Even if it's for pretend.

437
00:35:47,712 --> 00:35:49,047
Just for tomorrow.

438
00:35:54,419 --> 00:35:55,220
Okay.

439
00:35:59,424 --> 00:36:00,625
Junnosuke.

440
00:36:02,861 --> 00:36:03,661
Nami.

441
00:36:06,665 --> 00:36:08,667
It's just for today, but...

442
00:36:09,434 --> 00:36:10,502
Thank you.

443
00:36:12,604 --> 00:36:16,808
There's something I want you to see.

444
00:36:18,176 --> 00:36:18,977
Um...

445
00:36:21,346 --> 00:36:22,247
Let's go.

446
00:36:22,280 --> 00:36:23,381
Wait!

447
00:36:23,915 --> 00:36:25,517
Hold on.

448
00:36:26,317 --> 00:36:29,687
Not this way, it's...

449
00:36:29,721 --> 00:36:31,756
Look Nami, over there.

450
00:36:32,991 --> 00:36:34,159
There you go.

451
00:36:34,292 --> 00:36:36,694
- Wow.
- Here.

452
00:36:37,328 --> 00:36:38,797
Let's get a balloon dog.

453
00:36:39,230 --> 00:36:40,432
A dog?

454
00:36:41,199 --> 00:36:42,867
- Here.
- It's so cute.

455
00:36:43,802 --> 00:36:45,036
Thank you.

456
00:36:47,672 --> 00:36:50,308
Is this our first time
shopping together?

457
00:36:50,642 --> 00:36:52,177
We went when we went glamping.

458
00:36:52,210 --> 00:36:54,612
Not that kind of shopping.

459
00:36:54,979 --> 00:36:56,414
The first day we met.

460
00:36:56,748 --> 00:36:58,550
When we went to buy you clothes.

461
00:36:58,983 --> 00:37:00,585
Those expensive clothes.

462
00:37:00,618 --> 00:37:02,253
Seems like so long ago.

463
00:37:03,888 --> 00:37:05,590
I love sweet stuff.

464
00:37:05,623 --> 00:37:06,691
I know.

465
00:37:07,092 --> 00:37:09,794
You ate Kenchan's cake by yourself.

466
00:37:10,228 --> 00:37:12,063
Didn't you eat some too?

467
00:37:12,097 --> 00:37:13,898
Of course not.

468
00:37:14,065 --> 00:37:16,267
Then this is our first cake together.

469
00:37:16,534 --> 00:37:20,905
Actually, I bought one for us
one time.

470
00:37:21,673 --> 00:37:24,309
Stuff happened and
we didn't eat it together.

471
00:37:24,342 --> 00:37:26,311
What happened?

472
00:37:26,344 --> 00:37:29,013
Lots of stuff. Between you and me.

473
00:37:29,047 --> 00:37:30,281
There you go.

474
00:37:30,315 --> 00:37:31,182
Thank you.

475
00:37:33,184 --> 00:37:34,185
Bye.

476
00:37:38,156 --> 00:37:39,023
Junnosuke.

477
00:37:41,192 --> 00:37:43,795
The reason I asked you
to be my boyfriend today

478
00:37:46,064 --> 00:37:50,435
was because I wanted you to
see something before you left.

479
00:38:00,145 --> 00:38:01,412
A rental warehouse?

480
00:38:02,847 --> 00:38:05,283
Mr. Oashi brought me here yesterday.

481
00:38:36,281 --> 00:38:37,081
It's...

482
00:38:37,682 --> 00:38:41,953
Mr. Oashi didn't have the heart
to throw it away.

483
00:38:42,587 --> 00:38:43,488
So he kept it.

484
00:38:49,727 --> 00:38:51,896
This is from his last exhibition.

485
00:38:54,399 --> 00:38:55,400
This one too.

486
00:38:55,433 --> 00:38:57,702
These are from last year's.

487
00:39:22,727 --> 00:39:24,629
I didn't know he'd taken these.

488
00:39:25,530 --> 00:39:29,167
Mr. Jun likes seeing traces of people.

489
00:39:30,068 --> 00:39:31,903
Traces of people?

490
00:39:32,370 --> 00:39:36,241
He said he loves imaging
the people that were there.

491
00:39:37,308 --> 00:39:42,981
Somebody probably forgot this
after a party or something.

492
00:39:44,382 --> 00:39:48,620
Somebody dropped this rice ball
before they could eat it.

493
00:39:50,054 --> 00:39:52,290
Traces of people, huh.

494
00:39:54,692 --> 00:39:56,261
That day.

495
00:39:56,294 --> 00:39:57,795
Look.

496
00:39:59,163 --> 00:40:00,398
No way!

497
00:40:02,600 --> 00:40:04,168
I was there.

498
00:40:05,470 --> 00:40:07,472
Mr. Jun's photographs...

499
00:40:08,573 --> 00:40:12,477
They make me realize just how much
he loves photography.

500
00:40:13,311 --> 00:40:17,081
He was going to throw these all away.

501
00:40:17,115 --> 00:40:20,852
To try and forget
how much he cared about it.

502
00:40:28,059 --> 00:40:30,695
Remember what you once told me?

503
00:40:32,764 --> 00:40:35,099
That there's no use in dreaming

504
00:40:35,133 --> 00:40:39,704
if it holds you back
and keeps you from smiling.

505
00:40:43,408 --> 00:40:46,177
Those words really saved me.

506
00:40:48,179 --> 00:40:52,016
I felt like maybe
I didn't need to dream.

507
00:40:53,117 --> 00:40:54,252
Thanks to you.

508
00:40:58,022 --> 00:40:58,890
But...

509
00:41:01,659 --> 00:41:06,197
If you ignore your dream,
and that keeps you from smiling,

510
00:41:07,632 --> 00:41:09,667
I think that's useless too.

511
00:41:14,339 --> 00:41:16,741
I want you to keep smiling.

512
00:41:22,046 --> 00:41:24,248
Maybe that's what dreams are for.

513
00:41:26,484 --> 00:41:29,887
Because you want to smile
a whole bunch some day.

514
00:41:30,321 --> 00:41:32,590
So even if it's really hard right now,

515
00:41:33,257 --> 00:41:35,560
you can't help but dream.

516
00:41:37,962 --> 00:41:41,199
Because you want to smile some day...

517
00:41:47,672 --> 00:41:48,639
I...

518
00:42:02,587 --> 00:42:05,056
I love your smiling face.

519
00:42:41,392 --> 00:42:43,227
Kanazawa City, Ishikawa

520
00:42:45,396 --> 00:42:46,697
May I have a word with you?

521
00:42:47,732 --> 00:42:48,566
What is it?

522
00:42:51,235 --> 00:42:52,036
Father.

523
00:42:54,672 --> 00:42:58,276
I can't take over your company.

524
00:43:02,046 --> 00:43:02,914
I'm sorry.

525
00:43:04,215 --> 00:43:06,150
I want to be a photographer.

526
00:43:12,423 --> 00:43:13,658
Did you win an award?

527
00:43:18,096 --> 00:43:23,968
I'd run away from really trying
all this time.

528
00:43:25,770 --> 00:43:27,939
It might not work out at all.

529
00:43:30,608 --> 00:43:31,609
But still.

530
00:43:33,478 --> 00:43:34,679
I don't want to run anymore.

531
00:43:43,554 --> 00:43:44,322
Sis.

532
00:43:51,295 --> 00:43:53,297
If you wish for his happiness...

533
00:43:55,299 --> 00:43:56,868
Please.

534
00:43:58,035 --> 00:44:03,007
Let him live his life,
not for the family but for himself.

535
00:44:14,986 --> 00:44:19,090
Even if it doesn't work out,
it's not a waste.

536
00:44:44,048 --> 00:44:46,317
Letter of Resignation

537
00:44:47,051 --> 00:44:47,985
What's this?

538
00:44:48,386 --> 00:44:51,756
I'd planned on handing it in
once Miyavi was on track.

539
00:44:52,256 --> 00:44:55,726
From now, I wish to create
my own magazine the way that I wish.

540
00:45:01,566 --> 00:45:02,733
I understand.

541
00:45:03,467 --> 00:45:04,435
And...

542
00:45:05,803 --> 00:45:09,941
I've decided to start depending
on other people too.

543
00:45:10,608 --> 00:45:11,809
That's a good decision.

544
00:45:14,879 --> 00:45:15,713
May I...

545
00:45:17,748 --> 00:45:18,916
depend on you?

546
00:45:24,388 --> 00:45:25,890
Please support me.

547
00:45:27,024 --> 00:45:28,192
Do you mean...

548
00:45:29,827 --> 00:45:32,263
in a business sense, or...

549
00:45:33,230 --> 00:45:34,332
personally?

550
00:45:41,739 --> 00:45:43,307
The devil's grin.

551
00:46:02,393 --> 00:46:03,194
Excuse me.

552
00:46:08,799 --> 00:46:09,600
Ms. Horai.

553
00:46:11,469 --> 00:46:13,137
Thank you for everything.

554
00:46:14,105 --> 00:46:19,176
Who'd have thought
I'd quit earlier than you would.

555
00:46:21,712 --> 00:46:23,581
Can you handle an average job now?

556
00:46:25,049 --> 00:46:25,816
I hope so.

557
00:46:32,590 --> 00:46:36,327
I just want a normal average job.

558
00:46:36,360 --> 00:46:40,164
As long as you make light of odd jobs,
this job is too much for you.

559
00:46:40,197 --> 00:46:43,968
I won't run away anymore
until I'm average!

560
00:46:44,001 --> 00:46:45,970
My boss is not awful!

561
00:46:46,303 --> 00:46:49,206
Sometimes, she'll listen to
her assistant's opinion.

562
00:46:50,608 --> 00:46:52,810
What does it mean to protect Miyavi?

563
00:46:52,843 --> 00:46:56,814
If we can't make Miyavi the way
we feel is right, what use is there?

564
00:46:56,847 --> 00:46:59,150
I want Miyavi to stay the way it is.

565
00:46:59,917 --> 00:47:03,521
As long as you're here,
I'm your only assistant.

566
00:47:03,554 --> 00:47:06,023
I wrote a small article in it, too.

567
00:47:06,290 --> 00:47:08,793
I put everything I learned from you
in it.

568
00:47:11,262 --> 00:47:14,332
Thanks to you, I was able to make
a wonderful magazine.

569
00:47:18,502 --> 00:47:19,403
Thank you.

570
00:47:21,839 --> 00:47:22,873
Thank you.

571
00:47:24,375 --> 00:47:25,409
For everything.

572
00:47:27,745 --> 00:47:28,946
I'm finally free from you.

573
00:47:32,183 --> 00:47:33,317
Come on.

574
00:47:34,752 --> 00:47:36,120
And I was just about to cry.

575
00:47:37,588 --> 00:47:38,689
Save it.

576
00:47:40,725 --> 00:47:43,327
Junnosuke is leaving Japan today.

577
00:47:45,663 --> 00:47:47,431
He won't succeed Horai Paperworks.

578
00:47:48,899 --> 00:47:51,102
He's going to be a photographer
in Cambodia.

579
00:47:57,942 --> 00:48:00,678
Hey, hold up Suzuki.

580
00:48:00,711 --> 00:48:04,215
Come look at this.

581
00:48:04,248 --> 00:48:06,951
- A surprise party for Ms. Horai.
- I can't.

582
00:48:12,656 --> 00:48:15,493
I have to leave, now!

583
00:48:15,526 --> 00:48:17,995
But work hours.

584
00:48:18,229 --> 00:48:19,296
Suzuki.

585
00:48:22,533 --> 00:48:24,301
Someone's here.

586
00:48:33,077 --> 00:48:34,245
Junnosuke?

587
00:48:35,312 --> 00:48:36,147
Why?

588
00:48:37,214 --> 00:48:38,115
Nami.

589
00:48:39,750 --> 00:48:41,318
Junnosuke?

590
00:48:42,253 --> 00:48:43,420
Mr. Junnosuke?

591
00:48:47,458 --> 00:48:48,959
Stop staring.

592
00:48:57,635 --> 00:49:00,604
There's something
I wanted to tell you.

593
00:49:01,372 --> 00:49:02,873
Why are you here?

594
00:49:04,441 --> 00:49:08,012
I heard you were going to Cambodia.

595
00:49:08,045 --> 00:49:11,048
I was like, why Cambodia?
So I was going to go...

596
00:49:11,081 --> 00:49:12,883
I'm going to be a photographer again.

597
00:49:15,452 --> 00:49:20,024
I'll be a publicist photographer
for an NGO in Cambodia.

598
00:49:20,858 --> 00:49:22,526
And try to build a career.

599
00:49:26,864 --> 00:49:27,798
Okay.

600
00:49:29,834 --> 00:49:31,969
Thank you, Nami.

601
00:49:34,138 --> 00:49:35,739
You helped me make my resolve.

602
00:49:37,575 --> 00:49:38,776
I won't run anymore.

603
00:49:42,546 --> 00:49:43,681
Good.

604
00:49:45,816 --> 00:49:47,184
I'm really glad.

605
00:49:50,421 --> 00:49:51,322
One more thing.

606
00:49:52,623 --> 00:49:53,324
Yes?

607
00:49:55,426 --> 00:49:59,530
I want to be with you and smile.

608
00:50:01,065 --> 00:50:02,933
So I'll come back home
to where you are.

609
00:50:06,504 --> 00:50:07,571
Will you wait for me?

610
00:50:13,277 --> 00:50:14,211
That's unfair.

611
00:50:17,414 --> 00:50:20,317
You're always unfair.

612
00:50:27,291 --> 00:50:31,829
Of course I'll wait for you.
Till the end of time.

613
00:50:43,540 --> 00:50:45,376
All right, Suzuki!

614
00:50:45,409 --> 00:50:50,414
That's how journeys should begin.
You're so the man!

615
00:50:51,015 --> 00:50:52,216
Très bien.

616
00:50:52,249 --> 00:50:53,784
I'm happy for you.

617
00:50:54,818 --> 00:50:55,786
Congrats.

618
00:51:05,796 --> 00:51:06,764
I love you.

619
00:51:07,998 --> 00:51:09,566
More than anyone in the world.

620
00:51:12,836 --> 00:51:13,203
Me too. I love you.

621
00:51:26,106 --> 00:51:29,410
I'm going to charge up a whole bunch.

622
00:51:45,720 --> 00:51:48,390
Three years later

623
00:51:52,994 --> 00:51:53,628
To think you'd really make it.

624
00:51:53,628 --> 00:51:55,363
Hot-Cold Daily Calendar

625
00:51:55,397 --> 00:51:57,465
I hear it's already selling well.

626
00:51:57,499 --> 00:51:59,534
It was my dream to make this.

627
00:52:01,369 --> 00:52:03,872
Shut it, Suzuki.

628
00:52:04,406 --> 00:52:08,476
Nobody ever said this was you.

629
00:52:11,313 --> 00:52:12,981
There's your sweet side.

630
00:52:13,281 --> 00:52:14,549
Shut up.

631
00:52:15,817 --> 00:52:17,886
Come on, editorial meeting.

632
00:52:19,254 --> 00:52:20,255
Please, editor-in-chief.

633
00:52:21,923 --> 00:52:23,792
Good morning.

634
00:52:23,825 --> 00:52:26,761
The latest feature was a hit.

635
00:52:26,795 --> 00:52:30,665
Harry Winston wants to do
a ten-page tie-up now.

636
00:52:32,567 --> 00:52:35,403
But before that.

637
00:52:36,972 --> 00:52:38,540
Suzuki, got something to say?

638
00:52:49,417 --> 00:52:53,054
For the past three and a half years,

639
00:52:54,489 --> 00:52:56,691
thank you for letting me
work with you.

640
00:52:59,861 --> 00:53:03,164
I started out as nothing
but was able to become who I am now

641
00:53:03,465 --> 00:53:06,434
all thanks to everyone here.

642
00:53:09,938 --> 00:53:12,607
Miyavi is where my dream began.

643
00:53:13,675 --> 00:53:16,544
Thank you so much.

644
00:53:41,336 --> 00:53:42,470
Good morning.

645
00:53:42,971 --> 00:53:45,507
I'm starting here today.
My name is Suzuki.

646
00:53:45,540 --> 00:53:46,841
Nice to meet you.

647
00:53:47,609 --> 00:53:48,777
Okay, great.

648
00:53:49,978 --> 00:53:53,214
Ms. Newbie. I'm counting on you.

649
00:53:53,481 --> 00:53:55,850
I'll do my best, Mr. President.

650
00:53:58,787 --> 00:54:02,757
You still hadn't quit this job?

651
00:54:06,394 --> 00:54:10,398
I'm your only assistant ever.

652
00:54:15,337 --> 00:54:18,106
I used to think normal was best.

653
00:54:18,673 --> 00:54:22,978
But normal is what's there
without you noticing,

654
00:54:23,011 --> 00:54:25,313
but evades you if you chase after it.

655
00:54:25,947 --> 00:54:27,816
That's how I feel now.

656
00:54:29,417 --> 00:54:31,586
I thought I didn't have a dream.

657
00:54:32,120 --> 00:54:35,790
But I dreamed of smiling one day.

658
00:54:36,091 --> 00:54:39,794
And now, I smile because I dream.

659
00:54:41,429 --> 00:54:42,364
May I?

660
00:54:43,765 --> 00:54:45,166
Hello there.

661
00:54:45,500 --> 00:54:47,302
Hi. What's its name?

662
00:54:47,602 --> 00:54:49,471
Komugi? How cute.

663
00:54:50,338 --> 00:54:55,610
That day, Junnosuke gave me a ring
and flew off to Cambodia.

664
00:54:56,878 --> 00:54:59,981
He said he'd call
once he got settled in.

665
00:55:00,015 --> 00:55:01,449
But nothing since.

666
00:55:02,217 --> 00:55:05,887
I said I'd wait,
but isn't this a bit too long?

667
00:55:06,755 --> 00:55:12,093
I can see through his work
that he's doing well.

668
00:55:16,598 --> 00:55:19,768
- I'm home.
- What took you so long?

669
00:55:19,801 --> 00:55:21,603
You said you'd help me find a room.

670
00:55:21,636 --> 00:55:23,004
I'm sorry.

671
00:55:25,373 --> 00:55:26,641
Sis.

672
00:55:28,877 --> 00:55:30,278
Did you see this?

673
00:55:30,311 --> 00:55:31,679
Hello!

674
00:55:31,713 --> 00:55:33,548
Uncertified accountants here.

675
00:55:33,581 --> 00:55:35,984
What? Is that Kenchan?

676
00:55:36,017 --> 00:55:38,386
He quit being an accountant.

677
00:55:38,887 --> 00:55:40,789
He'd wanted to become a YouTuber.

678
00:55:40,822 --> 00:55:44,159
Every girl is my favorite girl.
Kenken here!

679
00:55:44,192 --> 00:55:46,394
Don't forget to subscribe.

680
00:55:46,428 --> 00:55:48,563
We're getting lots of subscribers now.

681
00:55:48,596 --> 00:55:49,898
Hey.

682
00:55:50,965 --> 00:55:51,733
Where is this?

683
00:55:52,967 --> 00:55:54,969
I think it's in Shibuya.

684
00:56:00,308 --> 00:56:01,342
Sis?

685
00:56:18,126 --> 00:56:21,162
Let's Go to Cambodia

686
00:56:36,911 --> 00:56:38,012
I knew it.

687
00:56:50,758 --> 00:56:52,227
I guess not.

688
00:57:18,553 --> 00:57:20,421
Fresh paint girl!

689
00:57:31,666 --> 00:57:32,967
Junnosuke?

690
00:57:37,472 --> 00:57:38,540
Why?

691
00:57:39,874 --> 00:57:43,211
I wanted to surprise you.
Didn't think I'd see you here.

692
00:57:43,244 --> 00:57:44,445
I'm the one that's surprised.

693
00:57:46,114 --> 00:57:49,484
I just saw that poster of that bench.

694
00:57:49,517 --> 00:57:50,351
Oh, that?

695
00:57:53,054 --> 00:57:56,758
I've signed a contract
with an agent I met over there.

696
00:57:58,993 --> 00:58:01,462
That was my first huge job.

697
00:58:04,132 --> 00:58:05,233
Yeah.

698
00:58:07,769 --> 00:58:08,903
I'm so glad.

699
00:58:14,509 --> 00:58:16,844
You really are like a hero.

700
00:58:17,645 --> 00:58:18,513
A hero?

701
00:58:20,648 --> 00:58:24,352
You show up
every time I want to see you.

702
00:58:26,421 --> 00:58:31,092
Do you know why I'm your hero?

703
00:58:34,495 --> 00:58:38,433
Because you're special to me.

704
00:58:46,174 --> 00:58:48,376
I'm home, Nami.

705
00:58:50,511 --> 00:58:54,048
Welcome home, Junnosuke.

706
00:59:22,844 --> 00:59:23,811
Come on, let's go.

707
00:59:36,658 --> 00:59:39,727
Fresh paint

708
00:59:44,432 --> 00:59:45,500
No way!

709
00:59:46,901 --> 00:59:48,202
Seriously?
